sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Silver Fusion Compatible PhaB gene with zif23-GCN4
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence includes the RBS (with the best compatibility for the use of zinc fingers), PhaB enzyme, zif23-GCN4, and a silver fusion scar tissue sequence. The silver fusion scar tissue ensures the binding within a silver fusion vector. The zinc finger is there to help with the binding and translation of the PhaB enzyme. PhaB is a biodegradable plastic enzyme for polyhydroxylakanoate (PHB).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michaela Hugie
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence is silver fusion compatible and has a zinc finger included.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: zif23
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Zif23-GCN4 engineered repressor (+LVA, C2000 codon-optimized for E.coli)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Variant of Zif23-GCN4 (see BBa_C2000). CDS has been optimized (via VNTI) for expression in enteric bacteria. ssrA tag (LVA) added.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Protein Engineering Gods from the Pabo Lab
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This protein should form a dimer and bind a specific operator site, thus repressing transcription.
